1
00:01:35,850 --> 00:01:38,280
[Too Young To Love]

2
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:41,150
[Episode 20]

3
00:01:41,880 --> 00:01:43,670
I'm just going home for a few days.

4
00:01:43,670 --> 00:01:44,960
-Are you on the bus yet?
-I'll be back soon, okay?

5
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:45,640
When you get there...

6
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,350
Do you really have to go?

7
00:01:46,350 --> 00:01:47,479
Remember to text me.

8
00:01:49,770 --> 00:01:50,539
Yeah.

9
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:53,210
Just a few days, okay?

10
00:01:54,070 --> 00:01:54,920
Probably...

11
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,130
about a week.

12
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:01,210
I'm leaving now.

13
00:02:09,889 --> 00:02:10,830
Excuse me.

14
00:02:11,470 --> 00:02:12,130
Hello.

15
00:02:12,740 --> 00:02:14,060
I'm a photographer.

16
00:02:14,490 --> 00:02:15,340
I just

17
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:16,960
took a photo of you two.

18
00:02:16,990 --> 00:02:18,050
Please take a look.

19
00:02:18,110 --> 00:02:19,790
I think it came out pretty nice.

20
00:02:19,790 --> 00:02:22,050
Would it be alright if I posted it online?

21
00:02:22,720 --> 00:02:23,120
Sure.

22
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:25,360
Thank you.

23
00:02:25,630 --> 00:02:26,360
Thank you so much.

24
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,480
That impressive?

25
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:30,040
You made it straight
to the final round of interviews?

26
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:32,170
They must be very impressed
with your work.

27
00:02:32,170 --> 00:02:34,570
That's right, that's your boyfriend.

28
00:02:34,710 --> 00:02:35,430
Yeah!

29
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:39,700
How did your video interview go
this morning?

30
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:41,030
I really outdid myself.

31
00:02:41,030 --> 00:02:43,310
And with Professor Ye's
recommendation letter,

32
00:02:43,310 --> 00:02:45,040
I'll definitely make it to the next round.

33
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:46,640
And that's my girlfriend.

34
00:02:46,660 --> 00:02:47,240
Yeah!

35
00:02:49,579 --> 00:02:51,800
Let's go watch the sunrise this weekend.

36
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,280
Sure.

37
00:02:52,590 --> 00:02:53,850
Where do you want to go?

38
00:02:55,030 --> 00:02:55,630
Hold on.

39
00:02:57,860 --> 00:02:58,860
My mom is calling.

40
00:03:00,230 --> 00:03:01,310
Mom, what's wrong?

41
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:02,560
Xiaole,

42
00:03:03,020 --> 00:03:03,450
your...

43
00:03:03,450 --> 00:03:04,200
your dad...

44
00:03:04,770 --> 00:03:06,000
Mom, stop crying.

45
00:03:06,430 --> 00:03:07,290
Tell me slowly.

46
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:09,900
While your dad was
moving renovation materials,

47
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:11,590
he fell down some stairs.

48
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:13,140
He's in the ER now!

49
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:15,170
The doctor said he hit his head

50
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:17,480
-and is in very serious condition!
-Mom, calm down.

51
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:18,090
Listen,

52
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:20,230
send me the hospital address first.

53
00:03:20,230 --> 00:03:21,310
I'm coming right now.

54
00:03:21,310 --> 00:03:21,680
Okay.

55
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:22,120
Okay.

56
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:23,660
What happened?

57
00:03:24,450 --> 00:03:26,110
My dad had a fall
at the construction site.

58
00:03:26,110 --> 00:03:27,020
I need to go.

59
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,140
Tonight?

60
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,400
It's so late.

61
00:03:29,420 --> 00:03:30,890
There probably aren't
any high-speed train tickets left.

62
00:03:30,890 --> 00:03:31,840
I'll take the bus.

63
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:33,150
I'll go back to the dorm to pack first.

64
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:34,880
You should get some rest early.

65
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,270
How can you take a bus?

66
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:46,120
Hello?

67
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:46,960
Auntie?

68
00:03:48,340 --> 00:03:49,220
Where is my dad?

69
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,150
Your dad went out

70
00:03:50,150 --> 00:03:51,610
and didn't take his phone.

71
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:53,960
Xiaole's dad had a fall in another city.

72
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:55,360
We need to rush over there now!

73
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:57,360
Can you tell my dad to drive us there?

74
00:03:57,530 --> 00:03:58,610
Don't worry, Lan.

75
00:03:58,790 --> 00:04:00,040
I'll have him come right away!

76
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:01,770
Tell Xiaole to wait at the gate!

77
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,060
Thank you, Auntie.

78
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:04,010
Okay.

79
00:04:23,830 --> 00:04:24,310
Xiaole!

80
00:04:24,390 --> 00:04:24,950
Lan!

81
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:27,070
What are you doing at the school gate?

82
00:04:27,070 --> 00:04:28,270
I called my dad.

83
00:04:28,290 --> 00:04:29,650
He'll drive us there.

84
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:31,040
That's too much to ask.

85
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:31,950
I can just take the bus.

86
00:04:31,950 --> 00:04:33,040
This is not the time for that.

87
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:33,600
Stop overthinking it.

88
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,400
It's settled!

89
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:37,390
Dad!

90
00:04:41,909 --> 00:04:42,570
Uncle Dong,

91
00:04:43,159 --> 00:04:44,420
sorry for the trouble.

92
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,270
Auntie? Where's my dad?

93
00:04:47,070 --> 00:04:48,680
Going to find your dad
will only waste time.

94
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:49,600
Get in, Xiaole.

95
00:04:49,620 --> 00:04:50,820
I'll drive you there.

96
00:04:50,930 --> 00:04:51,990
Thank you, Auntie.

97
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:53,500
Okay, thank you, Auntie.

98
00:04:54,390 --> 00:04:54,850
Wait...

99
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:56,480
you're going too?

100
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:57,040
Yeah.

101
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:59,320
At a time like this,
I have to be with you.

102
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:02,000
Aren't you still waiting to hear
if you made it to the second round?

103
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,120
They won't get back to me that quickly.

104
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:03,650
Let's go.

105
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:14,200
Buckle up.

106
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:19,480
Auntie,

107
00:05:19,870 --> 00:05:22,150
if you get tired later, I can drive.

108
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:24,650
Don't worry about it, Xiaole.

109
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:27,700
Save your energy
for taking care of your dad.

110
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:30,040
Your mom must be very worried right now.

111
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:31,360
When we get to the hospital tomorrow,

112
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:32,890
you'll have a lot to handle.

113
00:05:40,380 --> 00:05:41,040
Honey,

114
00:05:42,020 --> 00:05:44,150
why did you just leave a message and go?

115
00:05:44,790 --> 00:05:45,650
What happened?

116
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:47,720
Nothing.

117
00:05:48,159 --> 00:05:49,340
Lan and Xiaole are with me.

118
00:05:49,340 --> 00:05:50,210
I have to go now.

119
00:05:52,930 --> 00:05:54,440
Auntie, thank you.

120
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:05,680
Mom.

121
00:06:06,450 --> 00:06:07,160
We're here.

122
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:08,680
Which floor?

123
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:10,600
I'll go park the car.

124
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,240
You two go ahead.

125
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:12,040
The ER, right?

126
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:13,310
Thank you, Auntie.

127
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:14,360
Okay.

128
00:06:14,650 --> 00:06:15,780
I'll be right there.

129
00:07:18,870 --> 00:07:21,500
[Aoki First People's Hospital]

130
00:07:22,490 --> 00:07:24,340
[Outpatient]

131
00:07:46,230 --> 00:07:47,680
[Nurse Station]

132
00:07:47,820 --> 00:07:48,570
[Elevator Hall]

133
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:09,170
Look.

134
00:08:15,890 --> 00:08:16,810
Look at my dad.

135
00:08:20,350 --> 00:08:21,920
He was so young back then.

136
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:24,740
And look how happy my mom was smiling.

137
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:28,810
I must have been...

138
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:31,040
around six or seven then.

139
00:08:36,929 --> 00:08:37,620
Yi Lan.

140
00:08:39,909 --> 00:08:41,370
I think all these years...

141
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,460
I've never really taken
any photos of my dad.

142
00:08:50,690 --> 00:08:53,660
Then, when your dad wakes up,

143
00:08:56,020 --> 00:08:57,480
take lots of photos of him.

144
00:08:58,390 --> 00:08:59,120
I'm just...

145
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:04,220
I'm just afraid he will never wake up.

146
00:09:05,970 --> 00:09:07,500
Don't say things like that.

147
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,060
The doctor hasn't said anything yet.

148
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:12,910
He will definitely wake up.

149
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,620
The doctor said...

150
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:18,930
The doctor said there's...

151
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:23,910
a large blood clot in his brain

152
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:27,410
and a serious injury to his lower back.

153
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:31,340
The doctor said...

154
00:09:31,750 --> 00:09:34,140
if he doesn't wake up, then...

155
00:09:35,690 --> 00:09:36,300
maybe...

156
00:09:47,550 --> 00:09:50,840
[Aoki First People's Hospital]

157
00:10:07,210 --> 00:10:07,720
Dad.

158
00:10:11,490 --> 00:10:13,820
Do you know
why I love photography so much?

159
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:17,240
Do you remember

160
00:10:18,110 --> 00:10:19,530
that you were the one who bought me

161
00:10:19,530 --> 00:10:20,730
my very first camera?

162
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:23,580
At the time, you told me,

163
00:10:24,700 --> 00:10:25,450
"Xiaole,

164
00:10:26,890 --> 00:10:28,920
when Dad's not around,

165
00:10:29,970 --> 00:10:31,770
use this to capture everything—

166
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:33,240
the sad moments

167
00:10:33,370 --> 00:10:34,970
and the happy ones.

168
00:10:36,730 --> 00:10:38,860
When I get back from my business trips,

169
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:41,420
we'll look at them together."

170
00:10:44,130 --> 00:10:47,050
You haven't even had a chance
to look at them together with me yet,

171
00:10:47,050 --> 00:10:49,050
and you've hurt yourself like this.

172
00:10:52,330 --> 00:10:53,810
Please wake up soon, okay?

173
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:25,050
Let me do it.

174
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:03,480
Mom!

175
00:12:03,510 --> 00:12:04,000
Mom!

176
00:12:04,150 --> 00:12:04,880
Dad's awake!

177
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:08,360
Dad.

178
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:09,650
Uncle is awake?

179
00:12:09,670 --> 00:12:10,050
Tong...

180
00:12:10,050 --> 00:12:10,720
How are you feeling?

181
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:11,320
Hongming?

182
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:12,400
Hongming!

183
00:12:18,010 --> 00:12:19,670
How are you feeling right now?

184
00:12:21,070 --> 00:12:22,870
His vitals are recovering well.

185
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:25,960
Doctor.

186
00:12:27,170 --> 00:12:30,770
-Anything else we need to watch out for?
-Dad, how do you feel now?

187
00:12:31,450 --> 00:12:32,180
Pretty good.

188
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:34,770
Hongming?

189
00:12:35,730 --> 00:12:36,660
You're fine now.

190
00:12:37,180 --> 00:12:38,310
Stop crying, honey.

191
00:12:38,630 --> 00:12:39,720
I'm fine, aren't I?

192
00:12:41,780 --> 00:12:43,540
You're fine, you're fine now.

193
00:12:46,050 --> 00:12:47,840
Why haven't you gone back to school?

194
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:48,610
I'm fine now.

195
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:50,590
At a time like this,

196
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:52,250
who cares about school?

197
00:12:53,380 --> 00:12:54,120
Don't worry.

198
00:12:54,780 --> 00:12:55,980
I've asked for leave.

199
00:13:09,620 --> 00:13:10,410
Be careful.

200
00:13:14,180 --> 00:13:14,800
Come on.

201
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:21,270
Dad.

202
00:13:22,150 --> 00:13:23,100
For now,

203
00:13:23,130 --> 00:13:24,480
you can just focus on recovering.

204
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:27,010
I'll take care of
all your business dealings.

205
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:30,340
First time your son's ever had to
carry you, huh?

206
00:13:30,340 --> 00:13:32,670
He's all grown up and gotten stronger now.

207
00:13:34,390 --> 00:13:35,190
Mr. Gu, hello.

208
00:13:37,180 --> 00:13:39,440
I'll transfer the deposit this afternoon.

209
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:41,180
Regarding the sheet metal,

210
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:43,700
spray painting,
and associated labor services

211
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:45,630
we discussed earlier...

212
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:47,700
Yes, yes.

213
00:13:49,610 --> 00:13:50,270
I see.

214
00:13:51,790 --> 00:13:53,650
How about I come see you in person?

215
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:55,390
You're at the factory, right?

216
00:13:55,390 --> 00:13:56,790
Okay, I'll be there soon.

217
00:13:57,620 --> 00:13:59,510
Dad, I'm going to see Mr. Gu.

218
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:00,810
Go ahead.

219
00:14:01,060 --> 00:14:02,920
Call me if there are any problems.

220
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:03,900
I can handle it.

221
00:14:03,900 --> 00:14:05,090
Don't worry about it.

222
00:14:05,090 --> 00:14:06,290
Mom, I'm heading out!

223
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:07,660
Be careful on the road.

224
00:14:10,110 --> 00:14:12,370
Our son's getting more and more like you.

225
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,260
I didn't expect this kid

226
00:14:14,260 --> 00:14:15,860
to have a knack for business.

227
00:14:19,410 --> 00:14:20,550
Are you home yet?

228
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:24,330
[Yeah. Many of my dad's deals
weren't handled promptly,]

229
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:25,480
[and all of them are now
in breach of contract.]

230
00:14:25,510 --> 00:14:26,620
[I might have to go back to school
a bit later than planned.]

231
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:31,000
Lan!

232
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:31,870
Mengmeng!

233
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:34,580
Did you see
that trending post about Xiaole?

234
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:35,550
Xiaole?

235
00:14:35,870 --> 00:14:36,730
Trending post?

236
00:14:37,340 --> 00:14:38,480
What trending post?

237
00:14:54,940 --> 00:15:01,680
[Trending]

238
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:05,450
[A photo posted by a major blogger
involves a privacy violation.]

239
00:15:05,490 --> 00:15:08,880
[The man in the photo is married.]

240
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:10,800
[The male party involved
is preparing to file a lawsuit.]

241
00:15:15,290 --> 00:15:15,870
Ma.

242
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:17,360
Xiaole,

243
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,510
you're in serious trouble this time!

244
00:15:21,050 --> 00:15:23,200
What exactly is going on with that photo?

245
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:24,080
Did you make sure

246
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:25,220
to get permission before publishing it?

247
00:15:25,220 --> 00:15:26,810
I asked that girl.

248
00:15:28,830 --> 00:15:29,840
But...

249
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:31,890
it was only verbal consent.

250
00:15:32,150 --> 00:15:33,950
That's going to be hard to prove.

251
00:15:34,310 --> 00:15:36,960
This will very likely
affect your internship.

252
00:15:37,910 --> 00:15:39,110
What do you plan to do?

253
00:15:41,210 --> 00:15:42,410
Let me think about it.

254
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:43,790
Xiaole,

255
00:15:44,440 --> 00:15:46,570
the internet is a double-edged sword—

256
00:15:46,660 --> 00:15:49,120
especially for those of us
in journalism and media.

257
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:49,720
Ma,

258
00:15:50,520 --> 00:15:53,120
do you know any lawyers?

259
00:15:54,910 --> 00:15:55,510
Okay,

260
00:15:55,530 --> 00:15:56,330
I understand.

261
00:15:57,150 --> 00:15:58,410
I'll send you a number.

262
00:15:58,630 --> 00:16:00,180
Give them a call later.

263
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:01,840
Okay.

264
00:16:01,860 --> 00:16:02,610
Thanks, Ma.

265
00:16:04,990 --> 00:16:12,440
[L; Photographer]

266
00:16:35,390 --> 00:16:35,820
Hello,

267
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:36,590
Xiaole?

268
00:16:36,810 --> 00:16:37,730
Where are you?

269
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:40,720
I'm out

270
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:42,200
handling some business for my dad.

271
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:43,610
I've been pretty busy lately.

272
00:16:43,610 --> 00:16:45,410
So I might not be back for a while.

273
00:16:45,420 --> 00:16:46,980
Take good care of yourself.

274
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,330
About the photo...

275
00:16:50,420 --> 00:16:51,390
are you okay?

276
00:16:52,420 --> 00:16:53,030
I saw it.

277
00:16:53,170 --> 00:16:54,430
It's nothing serious.

278
00:16:54,510 --> 00:16:55,890
Ma is handling it.

279
00:16:55,980 --> 00:16:56,850
Don't worry.

280
00:16:56,970 --> 00:16:57,830
I can handle it.

281
00:16:58,500 --> 00:16:59,300
That's good.

282
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:01,000
I saw that...

283
00:17:01,470 --> 00:17:03,050
you deleted all my photos.

284
00:17:03,890 --> 00:17:06,089
Are you afraid of dragging me into this?

285
00:17:06,730 --> 00:17:07,290
Lan.

286
00:17:08,140 --> 00:17:09,569
What you need to do now is

287
00:17:09,599 --> 00:17:11,240
focus on preparing

288
00:17:11,349 --> 00:17:12,609
for your study abroad.

289
00:17:13,260 --> 00:17:14,869
Don't let this affect you,

290
00:17:15,089 --> 00:17:15,550
okay?

291
00:17:16,190 --> 00:17:17,089
It's okay.

292
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:19,280
Xiaole, remember,

293
00:17:19,310 --> 00:17:20,910
I'll always be there for you.

294
00:17:23,560 --> 00:17:25,530
Alright, get some rest.

295
00:17:25,980 --> 00:17:26,640
Good night.

296
00:17:40,810 --> 00:17:41,410
Mengmeng.

297
00:17:42,290 --> 00:17:43,290
Hello, everyone.

298
00:17:47,310 --> 00:17:48,510
Why didn't you reply to my message?

299
00:17:48,510 --> 00:17:49,640
I missed you so much.

300
00:17:50,350 --> 00:17:51,150
What's wrong?

301
00:17:55,260 --> 00:17:56,190
Where is Xiaole?

302
00:17:59,060 --> 00:18:00,070
Did you and Luo Ningzi...

303
00:18:00,070 --> 00:18:00,440
Stop.

304
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:02,460
Ning and I are fine now.

305
00:18:03,210 --> 00:18:04,640
It must be Tong Xiaole then.

306
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:05,840
What happened to him?

307
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:08,930
Well, Xiaole took a photo
of a girl before.

308
00:18:09,110 --> 00:18:11,230
She originally said she consented,

309
00:18:11,260 --> 00:18:12,520
but now she denies it.

310
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:17,650
So basically,

311
00:18:17,770 --> 00:18:18,510
a while back,

312
00:18:18,540 --> 00:18:20,370
Xiaole took a photo of a girl.

313
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:21,920
You follow?

314
00:18:22,610 --> 00:18:23,270
And afterward,

315
00:18:23,270 --> 00:18:24,510
the girl originally said

316
00:18:24,510 --> 00:18:25,550
she consented,

317
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:26,750
but now suddenly,

318
00:18:26,770 --> 00:18:27,770
she's denying it.

319
00:18:28,670 --> 00:18:30,720
In short, it involves some

320
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:32,280
portrait rights issues.

321
00:18:32,340 --> 00:18:33,320
Basically a legal mess, right?

322
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:33,940
Yeah.

323
00:18:34,260 --> 00:18:35,220
But it's okay.

324
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:36,580
He's already hired a lawyer,

325
00:18:36,580 --> 00:18:37,710
so it should be fine.

326
00:18:38,540 --> 00:18:40,590
Xiaole is really unlucky this time.

327
00:18:41,830 --> 00:18:44,560
Will this affect
his study-abroad application?

328
00:18:48,260 --> 00:18:49,680
Do you guys have any...

329
00:18:50,270 --> 00:18:51,360
other news?

330
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:54,760
If you don't know,

331
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:55,950
how would we know?

332
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:56,990
Yeah.

333
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:59,640
It's not like we're the ones dating him.

334
00:19:03,670 --> 00:19:04,830
Hello. Please take a look at this.

335
00:19:04,830 --> 00:19:06,630
Sign here if you think it's okay.

336
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:14,150
It's you, right?

337
00:19:14,290 --> 00:19:15,120
What do you want?

338
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:15,890
Hands off!

339
00:19:21,250 --> 00:19:25,890
[Camera 1]

340
00:19:23,510 --> 00:19:24,270
Go away!

341
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:31,510
[Lawyer Wang]

342
00:19:41,360 --> 00:19:42,290
Lawyer Wang, hi.

343
00:19:43,070 --> 00:19:43,550
Xiaole,

344
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:44,510
good news.

345
00:19:44,770 --> 00:19:46,400
The other party has withdrawn the lawsuit.

346
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:47,260
That beating you took

347
00:19:47,260 --> 00:19:48,390
wasn't for nothing.

348
00:19:48,810 --> 00:19:51,010
Later, I'll help you draft a statement.

349
00:19:51,040 --> 00:19:51,720
Okay, okay.

350
00:19:52,110 --> 00:19:52,680
Thank you, Lawyer Wang.

351
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:53,940
Really appreciate it.

352
00:19:54,790 --> 00:19:55,420
Okay.

353
00:20:16,850 --> 00:20:17,680
Xiaole,

354
00:20:17,710 --> 00:20:20,640
when you're done handling everything,
let's go out.

355
00:20:21,730 --> 00:20:22,540
Xiaole,

356
00:20:22,820 --> 00:20:25,510
I've received the enrollment notice
from school.

357
00:20:25,510 --> 00:20:26,550
How about you?

358
00:20:31,810 --> 00:20:32,940
Congratulations.

359
00:20:33,780 --> 00:20:36,720
I still haven't heard back about...

360
00:20:36,820 --> 00:20:38,620
about my enrollment notice yet.

361
00:20:44,270 --> 00:20:45,330
Congratulations.

362
00:20:45,890 --> 00:20:47,170
I'll come back today.

363
00:20:47,350 --> 00:20:48,360
After I'm back,

364
00:20:48,730 --> 00:20:49,990
let's go out tomorrow.

365
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:14,540
It's so beautiful.

366
00:21:16,150 --> 00:21:17,350
Compared to sunsets,

367
00:21:17,620 --> 00:21:19,220
I actually prefer sunrises.

368
00:21:20,210 --> 00:21:21,710
Sunsets are beautiful,

369
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:23,680
but they're fleeting.

370
00:21:24,810 --> 00:21:26,410
Sunrises, on the other hand,

371
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:28,920
once the sun comes up,

372
00:21:29,110 --> 00:21:31,030
it stays in the sky all day.

373
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:36,550
I think sunsets aren't so bad, though.

374
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:37,350
Because...

375
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:41,240
when the sun goes down,
there's still moonlight.

376
00:21:43,740 --> 00:21:45,540
The moonlight will be here soon.

377
00:21:45,640 --> 00:21:46,420
It's going to get cold.

378
00:21:46,420 --> 00:21:47,100
Let's go.

379
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:48,150
Let's go.

380
00:21:48,150 --> 00:21:49,210
It's getting dark.

381
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:51,080
It's getting chilly.

382
00:21:57,180 --> 00:21:59,110
You're leaving tomorrow.

383
00:21:57,550 --> 00:22:03,390
[Waiting for the wind—and for you]

384
00:21:59,140 --> 00:22:01,030
Should I pick up
a few packs of nougat for you?

385
00:22:01,030 --> 00:22:02,630
Then I'll preorder a few more packs.

386
00:22:02,630 --> 00:22:04,590
You can mail them abroad for me later.

387
00:22:04,590 --> 00:22:05,390
Leave it to me.

388
00:22:06,420 --> 00:22:06,960
By the way,

389
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:08,490
have you finished packing?

390
00:22:09,060 --> 00:22:12,030
It's still early. I'm not going abroad
until next week.

391
00:22:12,030 --> 00:22:12,980
You should still pack early

392
00:22:12,980 --> 00:22:15,110
so you don't end up rushing

393
00:22:15,140 --> 00:22:16,160
and forgetting something.

394
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:18,070
Why isn't the stall open today?

395
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:22,690
How am I supposed to
make my new wishes now?

396
00:22:26,070 --> 00:22:26,940
I promise

397
00:22:26,970 --> 00:22:29,340
I'll find the vendor for you, okay?

398
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:30,510
You have to find him.

399
00:22:30,950 --> 00:22:33,010
It won't work if we go to someone else.

400
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:34,710
Relax.

401
00:22:34,870 --> 00:22:37,330
With me around,
what's there to worry about?

402
00:22:41,770 --> 00:22:42,700
You're the best.

403
00:22:45,950 --> 00:22:46,920
Let me take that.

404
00:22:46,940 --> 00:22:47,670
Give it to me.

405
00:22:48,540 --> 00:22:49,200
Lan.

406
00:22:49,860 --> 00:22:51,000
Once you're over there,

407
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,080
take good care of yourself.

408
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:53,400
Auntie, you keep it.

409
00:22:53,510 --> 00:22:54,120
It's okay.

410
00:22:57,420 --> 00:22:58,500
Stay safe.

411
00:22:58,740 --> 00:22:59,800
Thank you, Auntie.

412
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:03,400
Lan.

413
00:23:05,620 --> 00:23:07,280
I want to say something to you.

414
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:10,000
I've bought a big apartment downtown.

415
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:11,300
Mom, what are you talking about?

416
00:23:11,300 --> 00:23:12,430
Never you mind!

417
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:15,450
Remember to stay in touch with Xiaole.

418
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:16,830
Auntie,

419
00:23:17,270 --> 00:23:18,730
take care of yourself too.

420
00:23:19,450 --> 00:23:21,320
Uncle, take care of yourself too.

421
00:23:21,810 --> 00:23:23,540
Call me if you have any trouble.

422
00:23:23,700 --> 00:23:24,580
Alright, alright.

423
00:23:24,580 --> 00:23:25,790
Stop dragging this out.

424
00:23:25,790 --> 00:23:27,050
Traffic might get bad.

425
00:23:27,470 --> 00:23:28,000
Let's go,

426
00:23:28,020 --> 00:23:28,750
or we'll be late.

427
00:23:28,750 --> 00:23:29,270
Kid,

428
00:23:29,630 --> 00:23:31,110
anything you want to say to me?

429
00:23:31,110 --> 00:23:32,530
Remember to bring me back toys.

430
00:23:32,530 --> 00:23:34,810
You must study hard
and behave, you hear me?

431
00:23:34,810 --> 00:23:35,480
Yeah.

432
00:23:35,650 --> 00:23:36,180
Let's go.

433
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:36,860
You kid.

434
00:23:43,270 --> 00:23:44,590
You talked to them for so long,

435
00:23:44,590 --> 00:23:45,960
and I didn't even get any time
to talk to you.

436
00:23:45,960 --> 00:23:46,550
Go ahead.

437
00:23:47,100 --> 00:23:49,510
I know you'll be busy with school abroad,

438
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:50,740
but no matter how busy you are,

439
00:23:50,740 --> 00:23:51,680
you must rest properly

440
00:23:51,680 --> 00:23:52,430
and get enough sleep.

441
00:23:52,430 --> 00:23:54,110
Eat and drink properly.

442
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:54,900
You're already too skinny—

443
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:56,430
don't lose any more weight.

444
00:23:56,790 --> 00:23:58,370
You don't wear your coat properly.

445
00:23:58,370 --> 00:23:59,700
What if you catch a cold?

446
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:00,900
There won't be anyone there
to take care of you,

447
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:01,960
and I won't be by your side.

448
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:03,310
Going to hospitals abroad is a hassle!

449
00:24:03,310 --> 00:24:04,560
Okay, I know.

450
00:24:04,840 --> 00:24:06,960
Reply to my messages right away.

451
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:09,300
Video call me when you can.

452
00:24:10,040 --> 00:24:10,890
Do you hear me?

453
00:24:11,070 --> 00:24:11,960
I hear you.

454
00:24:12,470 --> 00:24:15,200
You have to text me good morning
and good night every single day.

455
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:16,730
Check in with me wherever you go.

456
00:24:16,730 --> 00:24:18,070
Otherwise, I'll worry!

457
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:22,680
Don't get too close to other girls.

458
00:24:22,730 --> 00:24:25,280
Have you just met me?

459
00:24:25,310 --> 00:24:26,890
Fly over to see me when you're free.

460
00:24:26,890 --> 00:24:28,950
I'll fly back to see you when I'm free.

461
00:24:30,080 --> 00:24:30,740
Yes, ma'am.

462
00:24:31,370 --> 00:24:32,100
Pinky swear.

463
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:34,680
Pinky swear,

464
00:24:34,710 --> 00:24:35,890
cross my heart—

465
00:24:36,490 --> 00:24:37,350
no take-backs!

466
00:24:42,030 --> 00:24:44,440
If you two keep dragging this out,
you'll really miss the plane.

467
00:24:44,440 --> 00:24:45,110
Uncle, just ten seconds.

468
00:24:45,110 --> 00:24:45,720
Ten seconds.

469
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:46,200
Ten,

470
00:24:46,510 --> 00:24:46,960
nine,

471
00:24:47,370 --> 00:24:47,850
eight,

472
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:48,440
seven,

473
00:24:48,710 --> 00:24:49,190
six,

474
00:24:50,270 --> 00:24:50,640
five...

475
00:24:50,640 --> 00:24:53,640
-Enough! Hurry!
-Three, two, one!

476
00:24:54,550 --> 00:24:55,510
I'm going.

477
00:24:56,150 --> 00:24:56,940
Take care.

478
00:24:57,920 --> 00:24:58,440
Uncle!

479
00:24:58,850 --> 00:24:59,730
Drive safely!

480
00:24:59,870 --> 00:25:00,270
Okay.

481
00:25:01,510 --> 00:25:02,860
Don't go anywhere alone abroad.

482
00:25:02,860 --> 00:25:04,780
-Stay with your friends when you go out.
-Okay. Don't worry!

483
00:25:04,780 --> 00:25:05,090
Okay.

484
00:25:05,090 --> 00:25:05,680
Go back now.

485
00:25:05,680 --> 00:25:07,210
Okay. Drive safely, Uncle!

486
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:08,030
Bye.

487
00:25:08,360 --> 00:25:09,440
You have to keep me updated as well!

488
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:11,040
We'll stay in touch by phone!

489
00:25:11,070 --> 00:25:11,510
Bye.

490
00:25:11,530 --> 00:25:12,470
And don't go making friends
with just anyone!

491
00:25:12,470 --> 00:25:13,470
Okay, okay, okay!

492
00:25:43,900 --> 00:25:44,480
Hello.

493
00:25:45,890 --> 00:25:46,800
Are you

494
00:25:47,230 --> 00:25:49,020
the vendor who sells nougat

495
00:25:49,040 --> 00:25:50,320
at our school gate?

496
00:25:51,140 --> 00:25:52,000
Yes, that's me.

497
00:25:52,120 --> 00:25:53,180
What's the matter?

498
00:25:53,900 --> 00:25:54,700
It's like this—

499
00:25:54,700 --> 00:25:55,810
I went to buy nougat today,

500
00:25:55,810 --> 00:25:57,200
but you didn't

501
00:25:57,250 --> 00:25:58,510
open the stall.

502
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:02,540
Something happened in my family,

503
00:26:02,860 --> 00:26:04,200
so I won't be going back.

504
00:26:06,590 --> 00:26:07,950
You mean,

505
00:26:08,450 --> 00:26:11,050
you're never coming back
to sell nougat again?

506
00:26:12,010 --> 00:26:12,490
Yes.

507
00:26:15,710 --> 00:26:17,560
Sir, well,

508
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:20,390
I'd like to ask you for a favor.
